name: OAuth token flow tracking
summary: This dashboard shows the information regarding the flow of token in OAuth

title.@value: Add false value to isPartOfOAuthFlow field

source.@value:
rule "Add false value to isPartOfOAuthFlow field"
when
  is_null($message."isPartOfOAuthTokenFlow")
then
  set_field(
    field : "isPartOfOAuthTokenFlow",
    value : "false",
    clean_field : false
  );
end

title.@value: Authorization Server  issued a token for client

source.@value:
rule "Authorization Server  issued a token for client"
when
  contains(
  value: to_string($message."message"),
  search: "Access token issued for",
  ignore_case: false
)
then
  set_field(
    field : "isPartOfOAuthTokenFlow",
    value : "true",
    clean_field : false
  );
  set_field(
    field : "OAuthEvent",
    value : "AuthorizationServerIssuedAToken",
    clean_field : false
  );
end

rule "Client obtained access token"
when
  contains(
  value: to_string($message."message"),
  search: "Obtained Access token",
  ignore_case: false
)
then
  set_field(
    field : "isPartOfOAuthTokenFlow",
    value : "true",
    clean_field : false
  );
  set_field(
    field : "OAuthEvent",
    value : "ClientObtainedAccessToken",
    clean_field : false
  );
end

title.@value: Client requests access to protected resource

source.@value:
rule "Client requests access to protected resource"
when
  contains(
  value: to_string($message."message"),
  search: "Request for protected resource sent",
  ignore_case: false
)
then
  set_field(
    field : "isPartOfOAuthTokenFlow",
    value : "true",
    clean_field : false
  );
  set_field(
    field : "OAuthEvent",
    value : "ClientRequestForProtectedResource",
    clean_field : false
  );
end
end

rule "Protected resource  retrieved"
when
  contains(
  value: to_string($message."message"),
  search: "Protected Resource retrieved",
  ignore_case: false
)
then
  set_field(
    field : "isPartOfOAuthTokenFlow",
    value : "true",
    clean_field : false
  );
  set_field(
    field : "OAuthEvent",
    value : "ProtectedResourceRecieved",
    clean_field : false
  );
end

summary.@value: This is a list of all sources that sent in messages to Graylog.

description.@value: This is a list of all sources that sent in messages to Graylog. You can narrow the timerange by zooming in on the message histogram, or you can increase the time range by specifying a broader one in the controls at the top. You can also specify filters to limit the results you are seeing. You can also add additional widgets to this dashboard, or adapt the appearance of existing widgets to suit your needs.

title.@value: Drop messages without correlation id value

source.@value:
rule "Drop messages without correlation id value"
when
  is_null($message."CorrelationId")
then
  drop_message();
end

rule "Is client requesting access token"
when
  contains(
  value: to_string($message."message"),
  search: "Requesting access token",
  ignore_case: false
)
then
  set_field(
    field : "isPartOfOAuthTokenFlow",
    value : "true",
    clean_field : false
  );
  set_field(
    field : "OAuthEvent",
    value : "ClientTokenRequest",
    clean_field : false
  );
end

description.@value: pipeline  used for OAuth token tracing

source.@value:
pipeline "OAuthTokenTracingPipeline"
stage 0 match pass
rule "Drop messages without correlation id value"
stage 2 match all
rule "Add false value to isPartOfOAuthFlow field"
stage 1 match pass
rule "Is client requesting access token"
rule "Authorization Server  issued a token for client"
rule "Client obtained access token"
rule "Client requests access to protected resource"
rule "Authorized request for protected resource was made"
rule "Protected resource  retrieved"
end
